Hi, technically this upload doesn't squash a debbugs entry, but
I thought it might count anyway.  I happen to have uploaded an
eegdev version with udev rules migrated to /usr/lib to
experimental during Cambridge MiniDebCamp, in coordination with
Helmut Grohne's work on the usr merge:

  * Team upload.
  * d/*{postinst,postrm,preinst}: protect udev rule.
    /lib/udev/rules.d/60-eegdev-plugins-free.rules may disappear when
    dh_installudev will move files to /usr/lib in certain multi-arch
    setups, so this files needs protection using diversion before this
    occurs.  Upload to experimental so that dumat can catch regressions in
    the upcoming three days.
    Thanks to Helmut Grohne
  * d/rules: build --with movetousr.
    This moves the /lib udev rule to /usr/lib.  This can be safely removed
    once dh_installudev implements this change itself.
  * d/eegdev-plugins-free.lintian-overrides: new.
    Override the unrecognized diversion on the udev rule.

 -- Étienne Mollier   Fri, 24 Nov 2023 16:34:30 +0100

Today's upload migrated the package to unstable.  Some may have
noticed yesterday's message from Helmut about pausing usr-merge
moves (I didn't notice until after I uploaded the few packages
affected), but this category of migration turned out to not be
on hold, see the point three of Helmut's exceptions:

> Exceptions:
>  * With more uploads, more systemd units will move. While such moves may
>    trigger the new problem, I expect that to be rare.
>  * Continue fixing RC bugs, in particular those that are due to
>    dh_installsystemd or systemd.pc having moved to /usr.
>  * Continue applying DEP17P7 mitigations for udev rules. Patches for
>    these have been sent by Christian Hofstaedler and a few people from
>    the Cambridge miniconf. These are unrelated.

Have a nice day,  :)
Étienne.


